Posterior Probability Model

Note!! We do not have to calculate the normalizing constant!
We can note that f(Y=y) = 1/c.
Then, we say that


\begin{align*}
f(\pi | y) &= \frac{f(\pi) L(\pi|y)}{f(y)} \\
& \propto  f(\pi) L(\pi|y) \\
\\
\text{posterior} &\propto \text{prior} \cdot \text{likelihood}
\end{align*}

